                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/675d</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-26T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1244. Referring to the note which you presented to the Swedish Government asking
                    for various statements relative to exports of Sweden to Germany, believed to be
                    in contravention of recently concluded agreement, you are instructed to inform
                    the Minister of Foreign Affairs that the Government of the United States views
                    with serious concern the very great delay which is occurring in furnishing the
                    information requested by the Government of the United States in reference to
                    this important matter. The Department is informed that instructions similar to
                    the foregoing will probably be received by your British, French, and Italian
                    colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
